BUSINESS
=========================
Bush Advisers Press for Help for Insurance Industry

The Bush administration's proposal to have the government
pay at least 80 percent of any claims  resulting from
losses from future terrorist attacks ran into a storm of
criticism from lawmakers.
http://www.nytimes.com/2001/10/25/business/25INSU.html?todaysheadlines

-----

Some Suppliers Say Kmart Has Pressed for Deals

Kmart has been pressuring some companies that supply its
jewelry, food and other products to give it cash back and
make other concessions to help its own bottom line.
http://www.nytimes.com/2001/10/25/business/25SHOP.html?todaysheadlines

-----

Bayer Agrees to Charge Government a Lower Price for Anthrax
Medicine

Federal health officials and executives of Bayer A.G.
reached an agreement that would nearly halve the price that
Bayer charges the government for its anthrax medicine,
Cipro.
http://www.nytimes.com/2001/10/25/business/25BAYE.html?todaysheadlines

